text: Emil Nyeng (born 30 April 1991) is a Norwegian cross-country skier. He made his World Cup debut in February 2011 in the Drammen sprint race, collecting his first World Cup points in the 2013 edition of the same race with a 21st place. In 2014-15 he broke the top 20 twice, with 19th places in Ruka and Otepää sprints.
